{"title_page": "List of non-marine molluscs of Madagascar", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n[[File:LocationMadagascar.png|thumb|upright=1.2|Location of Madagascar]]\nThe '''non-marine molluscs of [[Madagascar]]''' are a part of the molluscan [[fauna of Madagascar]] ([[wildlife of Madagascar]]).\n\nIn [[tropical rainforest]]s of Madagascar, there is high [[biodiversity|diversity]] of species of terrestrial gastropods and many species has low [[population density]], so many of them are \"extremely rare\".<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/><ref name=\"Operculate\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Emberton | first1 = K. C. | doi = 10.1127/arch.moll/0003-9284/138/001-041 | title = Operculate land snails from three rainforest transects in northeastern Madagascar, with descriptions of nine new species and one new subspecies: (Gastropoda: Caenogastropoda) | journal = Archiv f\u00fcr Molluskenkunde | volume = 138 | pages = 1\u20139 | year = 2009 }}</ref>\n\nAbout 50% of land snails in Madagascar are related to land snails in Africa.<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/>\n\n== Freshwater gastropods ==\n\n[[File:Madagasikara spinosa shell.png|thumb|drawing of apertural view of a shell of ''[[Madagasikara spinosa]]'']]\n[[Pachychilidae]]\n\nthe genus ''[[Madagasikara (gastropod)|Madagasikara]]'' is endemic to Madagascar, 5 species<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Madagasikara spinosa]]'' (Lamarck, 1822) \u2013 the previously used name ''Melanatria fluminea'' being not valid, endemic<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\">{{Cite journal | last1 = K\u00f6hler | first1 = F. | last2 = Glaubrecht | first2 = M. | doi = 10.1111/j.1095-8312.2009.01390.x | title = Uncovering an overlooked radiation: Molecular phylogeny and biogeography of Madagascar's endemic river snails (Caenogastropoda: Pachychilidae: Madagasikara gen. Nov.) | journal = Biological Journal of the Linnean Society | volume = 99 | issue = 4 | pages = 867 | year = 2010 }}</ref><ref>Brown D. S. (1996). [http://www.iucnredlist.org/search/details.php/13021/all ''Melanatria fluminea'']. [http://www.iucnredlist.org 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.] Downloaded on 7 August 2007.</ref>\n* ''[[Madagasikara madagascariensis]]'' ([[Jean-Pierre Sylvestre de Grateloup|Grateloup]], 1840) \u2013 endemic<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/><ref>Brown D. S. (1996). [http://www.iucnredlist.org/search/details.php/13022/all ''Melanatria madagascarensis'']. [http://www.iucnredlist.org 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.] Downloaded on 7 August 2007.</ref>\n* ''[[Madagasikara johnsoni]]'' (E. A. Smith, 1882) \u2013 endemic<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Madagasikara vivipara]]'' K\u00f6hler & Glaubrecht, 2010 \u2013 endemic<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Madagasikara zazavavindrano]]'' K\u00f6hler & Glaubrecht, 2010 \u2013 endemic<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Madagasikara vazimba]]'' K\u00f6hler & Glaubrecht, 2010 \u2013 endemic<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/>\n\n[[Planorbidae]] \u2013 there are 4 species of ''[[Bulinus]]:<ref name=\"Stothard 2001\">{{Cite journal \n| last1 = Stothard | first1 = J. R. \n| last2 = Br\u00e9mond | first2 = P. \n| last3 = Andriamaro | first3 = L. \n| last4 = Sellin | first4 = B. \n| last5 = Sellin | first5 = E. \n| last6 = Rollinson | first6 = D. \n| title = Bulinus species on Madagascar: Molecular evolution, genetic markers and compatibility with Schistosoma haematobium \n| journal = Parasitology \n| volume = 123 Suppl \n| issue = 7 \n| pages = S261\u2013S275 \n| year = 2001 \n| pmid = 11769288 | doi=10.1017/s003118200100806x\n}}.</ref>\n* ''[[Bulinus bavayi]]'' - endemic<ref name=\"Stothard 2001\"/>\n* ''[[Bulinus forskalii]]'' - introduced<ref name=\"Stothard 2001\"/>\n* ''[[Bulinus liratus]]'' - endemic<ref name=\"Stothard 2001\"/>\n* ''[[Bulinus obtusispira]]'' \u2013 endemic<ref name=\"Stothard 2001\"/>\n\n[[Lymnaeidae]]\n* ''[[Radix natalensis]]'' (Krauss, 1848)<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Stothard | first1 = J. R. | last2 = Bremond | first2 = P. | last3 = Andriamaro | first3 = L. | last4 = Loxton | first4 = N. J. | last5 = Sellin | first5 = B. | last6 = Sellin | first6 = E. | last7 = Rollinson | first7 = D. | doi = 10.1111/j.1469-7998.2000.tb00625.x | title = Molecular characterization of the freshwater snail Lymnaea natalensis (Gastropoda: Lymnaeidae) on Madagascar with an observation of an unusual polymorphism in ribosomal small subunit genes | journal = Journal of Zoology | volume = 252 | issue = 3 | pages = 303 | year = 2000 }}</ref>\n\n{{Expand section|date=September 2010}}\n\n== Land gastropods ==\n\n[[Megalomastomatidae]]\n* ''[[Acroptychia mahafinaritra]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Emberton | first1 = K. C. | last2 = Slapcinsky | first2 = J. | last3 = Campbell | first3 = C. A. | last4 = Rakotondrazafy | first4 = J. L. A. | last5 = Andriamiarison | first5 = T. N. | last6 = Emberton | first6 = J. D. | doi = 10.1127/arch.moll/1869-0963/139/071-141 | title = Terrestrial mollusks of Andriantantely Massif, Eastern Madagascar, with descriptions of 36 new species<BR> (Gastropoda: Caenogastropoda; Pulmonata) | journal = Archiv f\u00fcr Molluskenkunde | volume = 139 | pages = 71 | year = 2010 }}</ref>\n* ''[[Acroptychia bathiei]]'' Fischer-Piette & Bedoucha, 1965<ref name=\"Griffiths\">Griffiths, O.L. & Herbert, D.G. 2013. New species of land snails (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from two isolated karst formations in central western Madagascar: Tsingy Beanka and Antsingimavo, with additional notes on other regional endemics. ''[[African Invertebrates]]'' '''54''' (1): 1\u201348.[http://www.africaninvertebrates.org.za/Griffiths_Herbert_2013_54_1_585.aspx]{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n[[Cyclophoridae]]\nthe genus ''[[Boucardicus]]'' is endemic to Madagascar, consist 199 species and 5 subspecies<ref name=\"Balashov & Griffiths 2015\">Balashov I. & Griffiths O. (2015). \"Two new species of minute land snails from Madagascar: ''Boucardicus monchenkoi'' sp. nov. and ''B. ambindaensis'' sp. nov. (Caenogastropoda: Cyclophoridae)\". ''[[Zootaxa]]''. '''4052'''(2): 237\u2013240. {{doi|10.11646/zootaxa.4052.2.9}}</ref>\n* ''[[Boucardicus ambindaensis]]''<ref name=\"Balashov & Griffiths 2015\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus anjarae]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus avo]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus hetra]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus lalinify]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus mahavariana]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus matoatoa]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus menoi]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus monchenkoi]]''<ref name=\"Balashov & Griffiths 2015\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus peggyae]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus pulchellus]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus tantelyae]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Cyathopoma anjombona]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Cyathopoma hoditra]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Cyathopoma iridescens]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Cyathopoma madio]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Cyathopoma matsoko]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n\n[[Pomatiidae]]\n* ''[[Tropidophora humbug]]'' Griffiths & Herbert, 2013<ref name=\"Griffiths\"/>\n* ''[[Tropidophora sericea]]'' Griffiths & Herbert, 2013<ref name=\"Griffiths\"/>\n\n[[Veronicellidae]]\n* a veronicellid sp. or spp.<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n\n[[Orculidae]]\n* ''[[Fauxulus josephinae]]'' Emberton & Griffiths, 2009<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Emberton | first1 = K. C. | last2 = Griffiths | first2 = O. L. | doi = 10.1127/arch.moll/1869-0963/138/137-167 | title = Pulmonate land mollusks from three rainforest transects in northeastern Madagascar: Part 1 of 2, with descriptions of 12 new species and one new subspecies: (Gastropoda: Pulmonata) | journal = Archiv f\u00fcr Molluskenkunde | volume = 138 | issue = 2 | pages = 137 | year = 2009 | url = http://www.schweizerbart.de/resources/downloads/paper_previews/73901.pdf}}.</ref>\n* ''[[Fauxulus tsarakely]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n\n[[Succineidae]]\n* ''[[Succinea masoala]]'' Emberton & Griffiths, 2009<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n\n[[Subulinidae]]\n[[File:Subulina octona 005a.jpg |thumb|150px|''[[Subulina octona]]'']]\n* ''[[Allopeas]]'' sp. 1 sensu Emberton & Griffiths (2009)<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''Allopeas'' sp. 2 sensu Emberton & Griffiths (2009)<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Curvella poutiersi]]'' Fischer-Piette, Blanc, Blanc & Salvat, 1994<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''Pseudopeas cf. [[Pseudopeas valentini|valentini]]'' Fischer-Piette, Blanc, Blanc & Salvat, 1994<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Subulina mamillata]]'' (Craven, 1880)<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Subulina octona]]'' (Brugui\u00e8re, 1792)<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n\n[[Cerastidae]]\n* ''[[Conulinus randalanai]]'' Griffiths & Herbert, 2013<ref name=\"Griffiths\"/>\n\n[[Achatinidae]]\n* ''[[Achatina fulica]]'' [[Thomas Edward Bowdich|Bowdich]], 1822<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Achatina immaculata]]'' Lamarck, 1822<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n\n[[Streptaxidae]]\n* ''[[Fischerpietteus josephinae]]'' Emberton & Griffiths, 2009<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella ambodipelomosiae]]'' Emberton, 2002<ref name=\"Emberton 2002\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella andriantanteliae]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella beandreana]]'' Emberton, 2001<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella betamponae]]'' Emberton, 2002<ref name=\"Emberton 2002\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella kelimolotra]]'' Emberton, 2002<ref name=\"Emberton 2002\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella kendrae]]'' Emberton & Griffiths, 2009<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella laninifia]]'' Emberton, 2002<ref name=\"Emberton 2002\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella lincolni]]'' Emberton & Griffiths, 2009<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella matavymolotra]]'' Emberton, 2002<ref name=\"Emberton 2002\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella minuseula]]'' Emberton & Pearce, 2000<ref name=\"Emberton 2002\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella ruthae]]'' Emberton, 2002<ref name=\"Emberton 2002\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella sahia]]'' Emberton, 2002<ref name=\"Emberton 2002\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella soulaiana]]'' Fischer-Piette, 1973<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella taolantehezana]]'' Emberton, 2002<ref name=\"Emberton 2002\"/>\n* ''[[Gulella thompsoni]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''Gulella'' sp. 1 sensu Emberton & Griffiths (2009)<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''Gulella'' sp. 2 sensu Emberton & Griffiths (2009)<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''Gulella'' sp. 3 sensu Emberton & Griffiths (2009)<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n\n{{main|Parvedentulina}}\n* ''[[Parvedentulina]]'' Emberton & Pearce, 2000 \u2013 ''Parvedentulina'' are endemic to Madagascar<ref name=\"Emberton 2002\">Emberton K. C. (2002). \"''Parvedentulina'' and edentate ''Gulella'' of Madagascar (Gastropoda: Stylommatophora: Streptaxidae)\". ''[[Archiv f\u00fcr Molluskenkunde]]'' 131(1/2): 67\u2013165. [http://www.schweizerbart.de/resources/downloads/paper_previews/73642.pdf abstract].</ref>\n\n[[Acavidae]]\n* ''[[Ampelita ambatoensis]]'' Emberton & Griffiths, 2009<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Ampelita andriamamonjyi]]'' Griffiths & Herbert, 2013<ref name=\"Griffiths\"/>\n* ''[[Ampelita beanka]]'' Griffiths & Herbert, 2013<ref name=\"Griffiths\"/>\n* ''[[Ampelita julii]]'' Fischer-Piette & Garreau, 1965<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/><ref>Emberton K. C. (1996). [http://www.iucnredlist.org/search/details.php/1158/all ''Ampelita julii'']. [http://www.iucnredlist.org 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.] Downloaded on 6 August 2007.</ref> \u2013 ''Ampelita julii soa'' Emberton & Griffiths, 2009<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Ampelita lamarei]]'' (Pfeiffer, 1853)<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Ampelita owengriffithsi]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Clavator moreleti]]'' Crosse & Fischer, 1868<ref>Emberton K. C. (1996). [http://www.iucnredlist.org/search/details.php/4960/all ''Clavator moreleti'']. [http://www.iucnredlist.org 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.] Downloaded on 6 August 2007.</ref> / ''[[Clavator moreleti]]'' (Deshayes in F\u00e9russac, 1851)<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n* ''[[Helicophanta amphibulima]]'' (F\u00e9russac, 1839)<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/>\n\n[[Charopidae]]\n* ''[[Reticulapex michellae]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n\n[[Ariophantidae]]\n* ''[[Kalidos gora]]'' Emberton et al., 2010<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Kalidos manotrika]]'' Emberton et al., 2010<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Kalidos manta]]'' Emberton et al., 2010<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Kalidos maryannae]]'' Griffiths & Herbert, 2013<ref name=\"Griffiths\"/>\n\n[[Helicarionidae]]\n* ''[[Kaliella crandalli]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Microcystis albosuturalis]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Microcystis fotsifotsy]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Microcystis vony]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Sitala burchi]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Sitala mavo]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Sitala stanisici]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n\n==Freshwater bivalves==\n\n[[Sphaeriidae]]\n\n* ''[[Eupera ferruginea]]'' (Krauss, 1848)<ref name=\"Griffiths\"/>\n* ''[[Pisidium reticulatum]]'' Kuiper, 1966)<ref name=\"Griffiths\"/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of marine molluscs of Madagascar]]\n* [[List of non-marine molluscs of Mozambique]]\n* [[List of non-marine molluscs of Mauritius]]\n* [[List of non-marine molluscs of Mayotte]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Cite journal | last1 = Emberton | first1 = K. C. | last2 = Griffiths | first2 = O. L. | doi = 10.1127/arch.moll/1869-0963/138/169-203 | title = Pulmonate land mollusks from three rainforest transects in northeastern Madagascar: Part 2 of 2, with descriptions of 21 new species: (Gastropoda: Pulmonata: Stylommatophora) | journal = Archiv f\u00fcr Molluskenkunde | volume = 138 | issue = 2 | pages = 169 | year = 2009 | url = http://www.schweizerbart.de/resources/downloads/paper_previews/73902.pdf}}\n* [[Edgar Albert Smith|Smith E. A.]] (1882). \"A contribution to the Molluscan fauna of Madagascar\". ''[[Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London]]'' '''1882''': [https://archive.org/stream/proceedingsofgen82busi#page/n455/mode/2up 375]\u2013390.\n* Van Damme D., K\u00f6ehler F., Andriamaro L., Darwall W. & M\u00e1iz-Tom\u00e9 L. (2018). ''The status and distribution of freshwater molluscs''. pp.&nbsp;29\u201341. In: M\u00e1iz-Tom\u00e9 L., Sayer C. & Darwall W. (eds) (2018). ''Chapter 4. The status and distribution of freshwater biodiversity in Madagascar and the Indian Ocean islands hotspot''. Gland, Switzerland: IUCN. viii+128 pp. {{ISBN|978-2-8317-1882-8}}. [https://portals.iucn.org/library/sites/library/files/documents/RL-2018-001.pdf PDF].\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Molluscs Madagascar}}\n[[Category:Molluscs of Madagascar| Molluscs, Non Marine]]\n[[Category:Lists of biota of Madagascar|Molluscs]]\n[[Category:Lists of molluscs by country|Madagascar]]\n[[Category:Freshwater molluscs|Madagascar]]\n[[Category:Molluscs of Africa|*]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n[[File:LocationMadagascar.png|thumb|upright=1.2|Location of Madagascar]]\nThe '''non-marine molluscs of [[Madagascar]]''' are a part of the molluscan [[fauna of Madagascar]] ([[wildlife of Madagascar]]).\n\nIn [[tropical rainforest]]s of Madagascar, there is high [[biodiversity|diversity]] of species of terrestrial gastropods and many species has low [[population density]], so many of them are \"extremely rare\".<ref name=\"Emberton 2009\"/><ref name=\"Operculate\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Emberton | first1 = K. C. | doi = 10.1127/arch.moll/0003-9284/138/001-041 | title = Operculate land snails from three rainforest transects in northeastern Madagascar, with descriptions of nine new species and one new subspecies: (Gastropoda: Caenogastropoda) | journal = Archiv f\u00fcr Molluskenkunde | volume = 138 | pages = 1\u20139 | year = 2009 }}</ref>\n\nAbout 50% of land snails in Madagascar are related to land snails in Africa.<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/>\n\n== Freshwater gastropods ==\n\n[[File:Madagasikara spinosa shell.png|thumb|drawing of apertural view of a shell of ''[[Madagasikara spinosa]]'']]\n[[Pachychilidae]]\n\nthe genus ''[[Madagasikara (gastropod)|Madagasikara]]'' is endemic to Madagascar, 5 species<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Madagasikara spinosa]]'' (Lamarck, 1822) - the previously used name ''Melanatria fluminea'' being not valid, endemic<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\">{{Cite journal | last1 = K\u00f6hler | first1 = F. | last2 = Glaubrecht | first2 = M. | doi = 10.1111/j.1095-8312.2009.01390.x | title = Uncovering an overlooked radiation: Molecular phylogeny and biogeography of Madagascar's endemic river snails (Caenogastropoda: Pachychilidae: Madagasikara gen. Nov.) | journal = Biological Journal of the Linnean Society | volume = 99 | issue = 4 | pages = 867 | year = 2010 }}</ref><ref>Brown D. S. (1996). [http://www.iucnredlist.org/search/details.php/13021/all ''Melanatria fluminea'']. [http://www.iucnredlist.org 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.] Downloaded on 7 August 2007.</ref>\n* ''[[Madagasikara madagascariensis]]'' ([[Jean-Pierre Sylvestre de Grateloup|Grateloup]], 1840) - endemic<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/><ref>Brown D. S. (1996). [http://www.iucnredlist.org/search/details.php/13022/all ''Melanatria madagascarensis'']. [http://www.iucnredlist.org 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.] Downloaded on 7 August 2007.</ref>\n* ''[[Madagasikara johnsoni]]'' (E. A. Smith, 1882) - endemic<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Madagasikara vivipara]]'' K\u00f6hler & Glaubrecht, 2010 - endemic<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Madagasikara zazavavindrano]]'' K\u00f6hler & Glaubrecht, 2010 - endemic<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Madagasikara vazimba]]'' K\u00f6hler & Glaubrecht, 2010 - endemic<ref name=\"Koehler 2010\"/>\n\n[[Planorbidae]] - there are 4 species of ''[[Bulinus]]:<ref name=\"Stothard 2001\">{{Cite journal \n| last1 = Stothard | first1 = J. R. \n| last2 = Br\u00e9mond | first2 = P. \n| last3 = Andriamaro | first3 = L. \n| last4 = Sellin | first4 = B. \n| last5 = Sellin | first5 = E. \n| last6 = Rollinson | first6 = D. \n| title = Bulinus species on Madagascar: Molecular evolution, genetic markers and compatibility with Schistosoma haematobium \n| journal = Parasitology \n| volume = 123 Suppl \n| issue = 7 \n| pages = S261\u2013S275 \n| year = 2001 \n| pmid = 11769288 | doi=10.1017/s003118200100806x\n}}.</ref>\n* ''[[Bulinus bavayi]]'' - endemic<ref name=\"Stothard 2001\"/>\n* ''[[Bulinus forskalii]]'' - introduced<ref name=\"Stothard 2001\"/>\n* ''[[Bulinus liratus]]'' - endemic<ref name=\"Stothard 2001\"/>\n* ''[[Bulinus obtusispira]]'' - endemic<ref name=\"Stothard 2001\"/>\n\n[[Lymnaeidae]]\n* ''[[Radix natalensis]]'' (Krauss, 1848)<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Stothard | first1 = J. R. | last2 = Bremond | first2 = P. | last3 = Andriamaro | first3 = L. | last4 = Loxton | first4 = N. J. | last5 = Sellin | first5 = B. | last6 = Sellin | first6 = E. | last7 = Rollinson | first7 = D. | doi = 10.1111/j.1469-7998.2000.tb00625.x | title = Molecular characterization of the freshwater snail Lymnaea natalensis (Gastropoda: Lymnaeidae) on Madagascar with an observation of an unusual polymorphism in ribosomal small subunit genes | journal = Journal of Zoology | volume = 252 | issue = 3 | pages = 303 | year = 2000 }}</ref>\n\n{{Expand section|date=September 2010}}\n\n== Land gastropods ==\n\n[[Megalomastomatidae]]\n* ''[[Acroptychia mahafinaritra]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Emberton | first1 = K. C. | last2 = Slapcinsky | first2 = J. | last3 = Campbell | first3 = C. A. | last4 = Rakotondrazafy | first4 = J. L. A. | last5 = Andriamiarison | first5 = T. N. | last6 = Emberton | first6 = J. D. | doi = 10.1127/arch.moll/1869-0963/139/071-141 | title = Terrestrial mollusks of Andriantantely Massif, Eastern Madagascar, with descriptions of 36 new species<BR> (Gastropoda: Caenogastropoda; Pulmonata) | journal = Archiv f\u00fcr Molluskenkunde | volume = 139 | pages = 71 | year = 2010 }}</ref>\n* ''[[Acroptychia bathiei]]'' Fischer-Piette & Bedoucha, 1965<ref name=\"Griffiths\">Griffiths, O.L. & Herbert, D.G. 2013. New species of land snails (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from two isolated karst formations in central western Madagascar: Tsingy Beanka and Antsingimavo, with additional notes on other regional endemics. ''[[African Invertebrates]]'' '''54''' (1): 1-48.[http://www.africaninvertebrates.org.za/Griffiths_Herbert_2013_54_1_585.aspx]{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n[[Cyclophoridae]]\nthe genus ''[[Boucardicus]]'' is endemic to Madagascar, consist 199 species and 5 subspecies<ref name=\"Balashov & Griffiths 2015\">Balashov I. & Griffiths O. (2015). \"Two new species of minute land snails from Madagascar: ''Boucardicus monchenkoi'' sp. nov. and ''B. ambindaensis'' sp. nov. (Caenogastropoda: Cyclophoridae)\". ''[[Zootaxa]]''. '''4052'''(2): 237-240. {{doi|10.11646/zootaxa.4052.2.9}}</ref>\n* ''[[Boucardicus ambindaensis]]''<ref name=\"Balashov & Griffiths 2015\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus anjarae]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus avo]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus hetra]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus lalinify]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus mahavariana]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus matoatoa]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus menoi]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus monchenkoi]]''<ref name=\"Balashov & Griffiths 2015\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus peggyae]]''<ref name=\"Emberton 2010\"/>\n* ''[[Boucardicus pulchellus]]''<ref name=