{"title_page": "Titz", "text_new": "{{About|the municipality in Germany|the German composer|Anton Ferdinand Titz|the German football manager|Christian Titz}}\n{{Infobox German location\n|type               = Gemeinde\n|name              = Titz\n|image_coa            =DEU Titz COA.svg\n|coordinates       = {{coord|51|0|22|N|6|25|27|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|image_plan          = Titz in DN.svg\n|state        = North Rhine-Westphalia\n|region  = K\u00f6ln\n|district             = D\u00fcren\n|elevation              = 95\n|area            = 69\n|population         = 8480\n|Stand             = 2004-12-30\n|postal_code               = 52445\n|area_code           = 02463<br>02164 (Jackerath)\n|licence               = DN\n|Gemeindeschl\u00fcssel = 05 3 58 056\n|divisions        = 16\n|website           = [http://www.gemeinde-titz.de/ www.gemeinde-titz.de]\n|mayor    = J\u00fcrgen Frantzen\n}}\n\n'''Titz''' is a municipality in the [[D\u00fcren (district)|district of D\u00fcren]] in the state of [[North Rhine-Westphalia]], [[Germany]]. It is located approximately 10&nbsp;km north-east of [[J\u00fclich]] and 20&nbsp;km south of [[M\u00f6nchengladbach]].\n\nSince the local government reform of 1975, Titz Municipality consists from 16 districts: Ameln, Bettenhoven, Gevelsdorf, Hasselsweiler, H\u00f6llen, Hompesch, Jackerath, Kalrath, M\u00fcntz, M\u00fcndt, Opherten, Ralshoven, R\u00f6dingen, Sevenich, Spiel and Titz.\n\n==Museum==\n* The [[LVR-Cultural Centre Village Synagogue R\u00f6dingen]] is dedicated to Jewish Life in rural Rhineland of past and present\n\n==Notable persons==\n*[[Petra Hammesfahr]] (b. 1951), bestselling German [[novelist]]\n\n<br>\n[[Image:Titz, kerk 2009-08-15 13.58.JPG|thumb|150px|left]]\n{{Cities and towns in D\u00fcren (district)}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:D\u00fcren (district)]]\n\n\n{{D\u00fcren-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{About|the municipality in Germany|the German composer|Anton Ferdinand Titz|the German football manager|Christian Titz}}\n{{Infobox German location\n|type               = Gemeinde\n|name              = Titz\n|image_coa            =DEU Titz COA.svg\n|coordinates       = {{coord|51|0|22|N|6|25|27|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|image_plan          = Titz in DN.svg\n|state        = North Rhine-Westphalia\n|region  = K\u00f6ln\n|district             = D\u00fcren\n|elevation              = 95\n|area            = 69\n|population         = 8480\n|Stand             = 2004-12-30\n|postal_code               = 52445\n|area_code           = 02463<br>02164 (Jackerath)\n|licence               = DN\n|Gemeindeschl\u00fcssel = 05 3 58 056\n|divisions        = 16\n|Stra\u00dfe            = Landstra\u00dfe 4\n|website           = [http://www.gemeinde-titz.de/ www.gemeinde-titz.de]\n|mayor    = J\u00fcrgen Frantzen\n|Ortsvorsteher     = Norbert Schiffer\n}}\n\n'''Titz''' is a municipality in the [[D\u00fcren (district)|district of D\u00fcren]] in the state of [[North Rhine-Westphalia]], [[Germany]]. It is located approximately 10&nbsp;km north-east of [[J\u00fclich]] and 20&nbsp;km south of [[M\u00f6nchengladbach]].\n\nSince the local government reform of 1975, Titz Municipality consists from 16 districts: Ameln, Bettenhoven, Gevelsdorf, Hasselsweiler, H\u00f6llen, Hompesch, Jackerath, Kalrath, M\u00fcntz, M\u00fcndt, Opherten, Ralshoven, R\u00f6dingen, Sevenich, Spiel and Titz.\n\n==Museum==\n* The [[LVR-Cultural Centre Village Synagogue R\u00f6dingen]] is dedicated to Jewish Life in rural Rhineland of past and present\n\n==Notable persons==\n*[[Petra Hammesfahr]] (b. 1951), bestselling German [[novelist]]\n\n<br>\n[[Image:Titz, kerk 2009-08-15 13.58.JPG|thumb|150px|left]]\n{{Cities and towns in D\u00fcren (district)}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:D\u00fcren (district)]]\n\n\n{{D\u00fcren-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Titz"}
{"title_page": "Barbara Horawianka", "text_new": "{{short description|Polish actress}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image = Barbara Horawianka.JPG\n| name        = Barbara Horawianka\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1930|5|14|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Katowice]], Poland\n| death_date   = \n| death_place  = \n| occupation  = Actress\n| yearsactive = 1955-present\n}}\n\n'''Barbara Horawianka''' (born 14 May 1930) is a Polish film actress.<ref name=\"filmpolski\">{{cite web |url=http://www.filmpolski.pl/fp/index.php/113071 |title=Barbara Horawianka |accessdate=15 November 2012 |work=filmpolski}}</ref> She has appeared in more than 35 films and television shows since 1955.\n\n==Selected filmography==\n* ''[[Tonight a City Will Die]]'' (1961)\n* ''[[Passenger (1963 film)|Passenger]]'' (1963)\n* ''[[Stawka wi\u0119ksza ni\u017c \u017cycie]]'' (1967)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDB name|0394559|Barbara Horawianka}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Horawianka, Barbara}}\n[[Category:1930 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Polish film actresses]]\n[[Category:Polish stage actresses]]\n[[Category:People from Katowice]]\n[[Category:20th-century Polish actresses]]\n[[Category:Knights of the Order of Polonia Restituta]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Silver Cross of Merit (Poland)]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Silver Medal for Merit to Culture \u2013 Gloria Artis]]\n{{Poland-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Polish actress}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image = Barbara Horawianka.JPG\n| name        = Barbara Horawianka\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1930|5|14|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Katowice]], Poland\n| death_date   = \n| death_place  = \n| occupation  = Actress\n| yearsactive = 1955-present\n}}\n\n'''Barbara Horawianka''' (born 14 May 1930) is a Polish film actress.<ref name=\"filmpolski\">{{cite web |url=http://www.filmpolski.pl/fp/